=== Cardinal number ===
'''два''' (dva) ''m'', две (dve) ''f''

#[[two]] (2)
#:*Last: [[один]] (1)
#:*Next: [[три]] (3)

*''Usage note: '''''два''''' and '''''две''''', when in the [[nominative case]], even in compounds (22, 32, 42, 102, etc.), govern the [[genitive]] [[singular]] of the noun.''
:два [[мальчик|мальчика]] — ''two boys (lit., two of a boy)''
:[[пятьдесят]] два [[мальчик|мальчика]] — ''fifty-two boys (lit., fifty-two of a boy)''
*''The reason behind the '''genitive singular''' here is that, in Old Russian, '''''два''''' governed the [[dual]] number, and the old '''nominative dual''' form was the same as the masculine '''genitive singular'''. When the dual number was lost in Russian, the form came to be considered the genitive singular that it resembled. This was extended to include the numbers ''[[три]]'' and ''[[четыре]]'', and eventually it was applied by analogy to feminine nouns as well.''
*''While the noun in a nominative construction is in the '''genitive singular''' following '''два''' or '''две''', an intervening adjective must be in the '''genitive plural''' or, less commonly, in the '''nominative plural'''.
:*две [[книга|книги]] — ''two books (lit., two of a book)''
:*[[У]] [[я|меня]] [[быть|есть]] две [[интересный|интересных]] [[книга|книги]] — ''I have two interesting books.''
:*[[У]] [[я|меня]] [[быть|есть]] две [[интересный|интересные]] [[книга|книги]] — ''I have two interesting books.''
:*[[пятьдесят]] две [[книга|книги]] — ''fifty-two books (lit., fifty-two of a book)''
:*Два [[маленький|маленьких]] (маленькие) [[мальчик|мальчика]] [[говорить|говорят]] [[о]] двух [[красивый|красивых]] [[девушка|девушках]] — ''Two small boys are talking about two pretty girls.''

